## **Step 5 â€” Sync cursor git rules into the new project**

Copy standard git rules from `common_project_work` so future commit/push requests work consistently:

```powershell
$src = 'F:\project_workspace\common_project_work\.cursor\rules'
$dest = 'F:\project_workspace\<project-folder>\.cursor\rules'
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $dest -Force | Out-Null
@(
  'git_local_push.mdc',
  'git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc',
  'git_commit_push_release_deploy.mdc',
  'git_new_project_setup.mdc'
) | ForEach-Object { Copy-Item (Join-Path $src $_) (Join-Path $dest $_) -Force }
```

Commit rule sync as a follow-up commit if the initial commit already pushed.

